HEADWORD: Achenium
<hw>A*che"ni*um</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr> }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/
to gape.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small, dry, indehiscent fruit,
containing a single seed, as in the buttercup; -- called a
<altname>naked seed</altname> by the earlier botanists.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>akene</asp> and
<asp>ach⟦ae⟧nium</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
